403
00:17:08.015 --> 00:17:09.905
I'll first go through a bit of background on the filter

404
00:17:09.975 --> 00:17:11.265
that the department operates.

405
00:17:12.045 --> 00:17:14.385
The department administers the classification act

406
00:17:14.725 --> 00:17:17.785
and this sets out what material is considered objectionable

407
00:17:17.805 --> 00:17:20.385
or illegal, such as child sexual abuse material,

408
00:17:20.915 --> 00:17:23.345
which we often refer to as CS A.

409
00:17:24.525 --> 00:17:28.025
We also operate the digital child exploitation filtering

410
00:17:28.025 --> 00:17:29.945
system to prevent and deter access

411
00:17:29.945 --> 00:17:31.465
to child sexual abuse material.

412
00:17:31.525 --> 00:17:33.025
And we call this D SEFs.

413
00:17:33.925 --> 00:17:37.185
The D SEFs blocks access to webpages identified

414
00:17:37.185 --> 00:17:38.185
as hosting CS a

415
00:17:38.645 --> 00:17:42.905
and as one of several tools that we use to take, uh,

416
00:17:42.925 --> 00:17:44.265
to address this type of content.

417
00:17:45.935 --> 00:17:47.715
It is an early intervention

418
00:17:48.095 --> 00:17:51.965
to stop people from inadvertent low motivation access

419
00:17:51.965 --> 00:17:54.805
to CS a and enables an education response

420
00:17:54.905 --> 00:17:56.885
for people curious about this content,

421
00:17:58.505 --> 00:18:01.125
the filter will not stop the most determined people

422
00:18:01.125 --> 00:18:02.245
from accessing this content.

423
00:18:02.305 --> 00:18:04.845
And for those people, we must rely on different approaches.

424
00:18:06.165 --> 00:18:09.535
Many internet service providers are voluntarily using DCFS

425
00:18:09.535 --> 00:18:12.375
on their services, and this covers about 95%

426
00:18:12.395 --> 00:18:13.895
of internet users in New Zealand.

427
00:18:14.995 --> 00:18:16.895
The voluntary takeup of the filter works

428
00:18:17.005 --> 00:18:20.535
because child sexual abuse material can be confidently

429
00:18:20.935 --> 00:18:24.455
identified and is universally considered to be abhor.

430
00:18:26.525 --> 00:18:29.225
The filter will soon undergo a significant upgrade

431
00:18:29.225 --> 00:18:31.345
through an agreement with the Internet Watch Foundation,

432
00:18:31.515 --> 00:18:33.545
which we expect to be operational in the first

433
00:18:33.545 --> 00:18:34.665
quarter of next year.

434
00:18:35.895 --> 00:18:37.905
This upgrade will increase the size

435
00:18:37.905 --> 00:18:40.785
of the department's filter list from a few hundred URLs

436
00:18:40.785 --> 00:18:42.785
hosting CSA to tens of thousands.

437
00:18:44.085 --> 00:18:45.705
It will also reduce the time

438
00:18:45.765 --> 00:18:48.345
and resource required to manually update the list,

439
00:18:48.915 --> 00:18:52.385
which means our investigators can focus on the often lengthy

440
00:18:52.765 --> 00:18:55.465
and highly sensitive investigations into digital

441
00:18:55.675 --> 00:18:56.825
child exploitation.

442
00:18:59.095 --> 00:19:01.115
Our assessment of the petition's request is

443
00:19:01.115 --> 00:19:03.715
that the changes would be a significant departure from the

444
00:19:03.715 --> 00:19:05.675
current voluntary arrangement.

445
00:19:07.055 --> 00:19:09.155
The scope of the change requested in the petition would

446
00:19:09.155 --> 00:19:11.955
require legislative amendments to the Classification Act

447
00:19:11.975 --> 00:19:14.515
and likely consequential amendments to other acts.

448
00:19:15.655 --> 00:19:18.915
The classification Act was enacted in 1993 well

449
00:19:19.015 --> 00:19:21.235
before the internet as we know it today.

450
00:19:22.095 --> 00:19:24.035
The ACT does not include provisions

451
00:19:24.135 --> 00:19:26.235
for a mandated internet filtering system,

452
00:19:26.895 --> 00:19:28.675
nor does it empower the government

453
00:19:28.695 --> 00:19:30.155
or direct, uh, government

454
00:19:30.155 --> 00:19:32.835
to direct internet service providers to filter

455
00:19:32.975 --> 00:19:34.875
and block content on their services.

456
00:19:36.135 --> 00:19:38.515
To do both of these things as requested in the petition,

457
00:19:38.515 --> 00:19:41.035
would require a clear mandate from Parliament

458
00:19:42.415 --> 00:19:43.805
under a mandated system.

459
00:19:44.055 --> 00:19:46.725
Compliance and transparency would also need

460
00:19:46.725 --> 00:19:49.645
to be prescribed in legislation to empower the department

461
00:19:50.025 --> 00:19:51.165
or other regulatory body

462
00:19:51.305 --> 00:19:53.765
to monitor the ISPs implementation of the filter.

463
00:19:55.385 --> 00:19:57.245
We are also concerned that extending the filter

464
00:19:57.265 --> 00:20:00.085
to more categories could unintentionally acc uh,

465
00:20:00.525 --> 00:20:02.405
restrict access to legal material

466
00:20:03.755 --> 00:20:07.965
rape am bestiality content sometimes will not meet the

467
00:20:08.165 --> 00:20:09.245
threshold for objectionable,

468
00:20:09.945 --> 00:20:11.805
unlike child sexual abuse material,

469
00:20:12.015 --> 00:20:14.485
which is always obviously illegal.

470
00:20:15.725 --> 00:20:18.985
For example, some adults consensually create content

471
00:20:19.255 --> 00:20:20.385
that depicts rape.

472
00:20:21.165 --> 00:20:23.015
Unfortunately, there are also incident

473
00:20:23.015 --> 00:20:24.815
where people will record real rape

474
00:20:25.035 --> 00:20:29.265
and share it as content differentiating between the two.

475
00:20:29.405 --> 00:20:31.785
And the effect of this content is complex.

476
00:20:33.045 --> 00:20:35.465
We could not confidently block rape

477
00:20:35.685 --> 00:20:39.305
or bestiality content in the same way that we do

478
00:20:39.305 --> 00:20:40.985
for child sexual abuse material.

479
00:20:42.125 --> 00:20:44.385
If we were to do this, we would run the risk

480
00:20:44.385 --> 00:20:45.665
of blocking legal content

481
00:20:46.245 --> 00:20:48.045
and violating the Bill of Rights Act,

482
00:20:48.045 --> 00:20:50.285
which includes the right to freedom of expression

483
00:20:50.345 --> 00:20:51.765
and access to information.

484
00:20:53.105 --> 00:20:56.005
So while rape and bestiality content are categories

485
00:20:56.025 --> 00:20:58.285
of objectionable material under section three

486
00:20:58.285 --> 00:20:59.405
of the Classification Act,

487
00:20:59.785 --> 00:21:03.405
distinguishing the two is a matter of careful consideration

488
00:21:03.405 --> 00:21:05.925
by experts like the department's investigators

489
00:21:06.065 --> 00:21:07.565
and the classification office

490
00:21:08.225 --> 00:21:10.605
and the this, their expertise is recognized

491
00:21:10.605 --> 00:21:11.725
in section four of the act.

492
00:21:13.225 --> 00:21:16.245
If rape and bestiality content were included in a filter,

493
00:21:16.315 --> 00:21:17.565
then we would need to consider

494
00:21:17.565 --> 00:21:20.965
what would be an acceptable risk of over blocking material

495
00:21:21.865 --> 00:21:24.565
and how would that be mitigated to protect the government

496
00:21:24.585 --> 00:21:26.845
and internet service providers from liability

497
00:21:27.425 --> 00:21:29.205
if legal content were blocked?

498
00:21:30.585 --> 00:21:32.285
The petition is noted in their submission

499
00:21:32.285 --> 00:21:35.205
that existing machine learning technology can scan

500
00:21:35.305 --> 00:21:38.325
and detect sites hosting rape and BCL content.

501
00:21:39.305 --> 00:21:43.085
We are not aware of technology that can do this to the level

502
00:21:43.105 --> 00:21:45.565
of accuracy needed for a government filter

503
00:21:46.285 --> 00:21:47.535
without human review.

504
00:21:47.545 --> 00:21:50.185
First, automated detection

505
00:21:50.185 --> 00:21:52.705
and filtering tools work better for private use,

506
00:21:53.325 --> 00:21:54.745
for example, in households

507
00:21:54.915 --> 00:21:57.825
where a higher error rate is accepted by customers

508
00:21:57.825 --> 00:22:00.505
because they are the ones exercising control over

509
00:22:00.505 --> 00:22:01.585
their internet use.

510
00:22:02.965 --> 00:22:05.345
The other complication with automated filtering is

511
00:22:05.345 --> 00:22:07.585
that developing filtering lists requires content

512
00:22:07.845 --> 00:22:08.985
to train the machine.

513
00:22:09.835 --> 00:22:12.745
Developing this technology in New Zealand privately would be

514
00:22:12.745 --> 00:22:13.945
difficult 'cause it would need

515
00:22:13.945 --> 00:22:16.545
to be trained on very large sets of images and videos.

516
00:22:17.485 --> 00:22:20.505
The Classification Act does not authorize proactive access

517
00:22:20.505 --> 00:22:23.465
to objectional material, including for the use of training

518
00:22:23.465 --> 00:22:25.145
and auditing a machine learning tool.

519
00:22:25.525 --> 00:22:27.545
And the department does not have the authority

520
00:22:27.645 --> 00:22:29.945
to grant legal access in this way.

521
00:22:30.885 --> 00:22:32.985
The classification office can grant exemptions

522
00:22:32.985 --> 00:22:34.225
for specific illegal content,

523
00:22:34.245 --> 00:22:35.785
but it cannot grant an exemption

